## Security

- All secrets via environment variables — never committed to Git.
- CORS configured to allow the frontend origin only (not `*`) in production.
- Firestore access only via backend service account — frontend never touches Firestore directly.
- Input validation via Pydantic models — FastAPI rejects invalid requests with 422 before hitting route handlers.
- Log sensitive data (API keys, user emails) at DEBUG level only, never at INFO or above.

